NAME
    gcloud alpha network-connectivity hubs update - update a hub

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha network-connectivity hubs update HUB --description=DESCRIPTION
        [--labels=KEY=VALUE] [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Update the detail of a hub.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     Hub resource - Name of the hub to be updated. This represents a Cloud
     resource. (NOTE) Some attributes are not given arguments in this group but
     can be set in other ways. To set the [project] attribute: provide the
     argument [hub] on the command line with a fully specified name; set the
     property [core/project]; provide the argument [--project] on the command
     line. This must be specified.

       HUB
          ID of the hub or fully qualified identifier for the hub.

REQUIRED FLAGS
     --description=DESCRIPTION
        New description of the hub.

OPTIONAL FLAGS
     --labels=KEY=VALUE
        List of label KEY=VALUE pairs to add.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --billing-project,
    --configuration, --flags-file, --flatten, --format, --help,
    --impersonate-service-account, --log-http, --project, --quiet,
    --trace-token, --user-output-enabled, --verbosity.

    Run $ gcloud help for details.

API REFERENCE
    This command uses the networkconnectivity/v1alpha1 API. The full
    documentation for this API can be found at: https://cloud.google.com/

EXAMPLES
    Update description of the hub named my-hub with description 'the new
    description of my-hub'.

        $ gcloud alpha network-connectivity hubs update my-hub \
            --description="The new description of my-hub".

NOTES
    This command is currently in ALPHA and may change without notice. If this
    command fails with API permission errors despite specifying the right
    project, you may be trying to access an API with an invitation-only early
    access allowlist.

